# Custom App Review Standards

When reviewing or auditing a Make custom app, follow these standards.

## MCP Servers

- **user-Make All**: Fetch app components, code, and coding/UX resources.
- **user-Atlassian**: Fetch latest UX guidelines from Confluence page ID `886734999` on `make.atlassian.net`.

## Key Resources to Load

| Resource | MCP Server | URI / Tool |
|----------|------------|------------|
| UX best practices | user-Make All | `file://static/custom-apps-ux-best-practices` |
| Parameters docs | user-Make All | `file://static/custom-apps-docs-parameters` |
| App API docs | user-Make All | `app_documentation_get` tool |
| Confluence UX page | user-Atlassian | `getConfluencePage` (pageId: `886734999`) |

## Review Checklist

1. **Spelling**: US English for all user-facing text (labels, hints, banners, errors).
2. **Casing**: Consistent Title Case or Sentence case per developer choice.
3. **UX guidelines**: Module naming (BP-011), descriptions (BP-001), hints (BP-002), messages (BP-015), array labeling (BP-016), ID finder (BP-017), field types (BP-004), date inputs (BP-018: date-only fields use type `"text"` with `help` for expected format e.g. `YYYY-MM-DD`), error handling (BP-022), pagination (BP-009).
4. **Coding practices**: Base config, communication, parameters, IML syntax, log sanitization.
5. **Unit tests**: Every custom function must have tests. Tests must follow quality standards: only `it()` blocks, `assert.strictEqual()` for primitives, `assert.deepStrictEqual()` for objects/arrays, no `assert.ok()`, descriptive messages when multiple assertions per test, strong deterministic assertions.
6. **ID finders**: Cross-reference API docs — any entity ID parameter with a corresponding list/search endpoint needs an ID finder RPC.

## Severity Levels

- **Error**: Must fix. Violates a practice or guideline.
- **Warning**: Should fix. Missing recommended practice.
- **Suggestion**: Nice to have.

## Output

Tag findings with category codes: `[SPELL]`, `[CASE]`, `[UX:BP-XXX]`, `[CODE]`, `[TEST]`, `[ID-FINDER]`.

Every finding for modules, connections, RPCs, and webhooks must also include the **block** it belongs to (e.g., `[communication]`, `[mappable_parameters]`, `[static_parameters]`, `[interface]`, `[parameters]`, `[api]`). Use `[module]` or `[connection]` for top-level metadata (label, description). Example: `**[communication]** [CODE] Missing log sanitization`.
